# HNZ Project Conventions

## Project Overview

Digital business card for Hila Noah Zablianov (HNZ), a CPA. Single-page React + Vite app optimized for mobile with Hebrew RTL support.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: React 19 (functional components, hooks only)
- **Build**: Vite 5 (ESM modules)
- **Styling**: Plain CSS with CSS custom properties (no CSS frameworks)
- **Language**: JavaScript/JSX (no TypeScript)
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions

## Code Style

- Use `const` for constants, extract to top of file
- Inline SVG icons (no icon libraries)
- Hebrew strings stay in source (no i18n layer needed)
- Mobile-first CSS with desktop media query at 500px
- BEM-like class naming: `.block__element` pattern
- Single-file component approach (App.jsx contains all logic)

## Important Paths

- `src/App.jsx` — Main component with all business logic
- `src/styles.css` — All styles with CSS variables
- `src/assets/hila-hero.png` — Hero profile image (imported by App.jsx)
- `public/vcard.vcf` — vCard contact file
- `index.html` — Entry point (RTL, Hebrew lang, JSON-LD structured data)

## Contact Constants

Phone, email, social links, and display names are defined as constants at the top of `App.jsx`. Always use these constants, never hardcode contact info elsewhere.

## Deployment

- Custom domain `card.hnz-cpa.com` — `base: "/"` in `vite.config.js`
- Build output goes to `dist/`
- GitHub Actions workflow at `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- `public/CNAME` contains the custom domain
